!Ardop

Hans is able to get Winlink to work on RPi / QMX / Linux

<<<
My ardopcf command line is:

ardopcf -G 8514 -c /dev/ttyACM0 -k 54583B -u 52583B -i 1 -o 1 -H "MYCALL G0UPL"

-k and -u parameters are TX; RX; respectively in ASCII, this lets ardopcf control the QMX transmit/receive using the appropriate CAT commands (I generally avoid the use of VOX wherever possible). 

-i 1 -o 1 select the QMX USB sound card. 
<<<

This is encouraging.  May show a path to winlink on my mac.

It looks like folks are using [[ardopcf|https://github.com/pflarue/ardop]] for MSWin and Linux, but [[nothing for Mac yet|https://github.com/pflarue/ardop/issues/130]].

